=== Pronunciation ===
[[Category:Hebrew language]]
נגע / nâga‛ / naw-gah'
=== Etymology ===

A primitive root; 
=== Verb ===
properly to [[touch]], that is, lay the hand upon (for any purpose; euphemistically, to lie with a woman); by implication to reach (figuratively to arrive, acquire); violently, to strike (punish, defeat, destroy, etc.): - beat, (X be able to) bring (down), cast, come (nigh), draw near (nigh), get up, happen, join, near, plague, reach (up), smite, strike, touch.